cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.AI 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tools and machine learning (ML) models for sentiment analysis in electronic health records (EHRs) of psychiatric patients. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and ML for language-related tasks. The paper also involves ML models, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper deals with clinical sentiment, which is related to healthcare, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) possible categories. Finally, the paper involves the adaptation of sentiment analysis to a specific domain, which is related to AI, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category.
